{"TopicId":182617,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mass Driver/Space Bridge","CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T10:04:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T10:04:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was wonder if someone with knowledge of how to put buildings into KSP could create a Mass Driver/Space Bridge like the one in Ace Combat 5 or 7. A working one would be nice, but I know that is next to impossible.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a picture of what it looks like btw:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222000?cb=20131103054713\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/acecombat/images/c/cf/49.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/2000?cb=20131103054713\u0022 width=\u0022558\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo get around the not working bit, maybe someone could create an indestructible sled with wheels? Or a part with so low friction that it can just speed up indefinitely?\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnyway, I would love to see this concept brought into KSP. Three would be fantastic, one pointing 90 along equator then one 45 \u002B/- from 90 degrees, but I would be happy with just the 90 degree one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T15:42:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223551408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551693859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277770\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GoldForest\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, GoldForest said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was wonder if someone with knowledge of how to put buildings into KSP could create a Mass Driver/Space Bridge like the one in Ace Combat 5 or 7. A working one would be nice, but I know that is next to impossible.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a picture of what it looks like btw:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/acecombat/images/c/cf/49.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/2000?cb=20131103054713\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222000?cb=20131103054713\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/acecombat/images/c/cf/49.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/2000?cb=20131103054713\u0022 width=\u0022558\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo get around the not working bit, maybe someone could create an indestructible sled with wheels? Or a part with so low friction that it can just speed up indefinitely?\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnyway, I would love to see this concept brought into KSP. Three would be fantastic, one pointing 90 along equator then one 45 \u002B/- from 90 degrees, but I would be happy with just the 90 degree one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried using Kerbal Konstructs?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T15:44:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPathfinder actually has a working one - for some definitions of \u0027working\u0027....\u00A0 (It can ship resources to vessels with a part to receive them with.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-05T02:33:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223551530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551714148\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried using Kerbal Konstructs?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t seen or I\u0027m just not seeing, what I\u0027m looking for with KK.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223551533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551714294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPathfinder actually has a working one - for some definitions of \u0027working\u0027....\u00A0 (It can ship resources to vessels with a part to receive them with.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s not the kind I\u0027m looking for. I\u0027m looking more for like a super long runway that curves upwards towards space. Like in the picture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: A super long runway that can support horizontally launching a rocket btw.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit 2: Something like this\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/41665-wip-mass-driver/\u0026amp;page=6\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EOld mod\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-05T02:39:27Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2019 02:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by GoldForest\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-06T05:06:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/77770-goldforest/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002277770\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/77770-goldforest/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@GoldForest\u003C/a\u003E No such mod exists that works at all or is designed for launching crafts along a physical ramp. You would have to build your own out of normal-looking runways in KK and it will have to be perfectly straight (no curves) as running across the bump or dip in the curve of a composite runway at supersonic speeds will easily destroy the ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-07T00:12:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSecond what Jade said about building it yourself, and not working with KSP\u0027s wheel physics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223551907\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551753236\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277770\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GoldForest\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/4/2019 at 6:33 PM, GoldForest said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit 2: Something like this\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/41665-wip-mass-driver/\u0026amp;page=6\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EOld mod\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo have a download source for that? It could be doable to at least get the model working in modern KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-07T05:31:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223553268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551917544\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSecond what Jade said about building it yourself, and not working with KSP\u0027s wheel physics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo have a download source for that? It could be doable to at least get the model working in modern KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I do not. I\u0027m not the mod author. And the author hasn\u0027t been on KSP in over a month. As for doing it myself, I have no modding experience really.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-07T05:32:27Z\u0022 title=\u002203/07/2019 05:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 7, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by GoldForest\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aesop1","CreatedById":191198,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-07T15:12:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223551533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551714294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/4/2019 at 11:44 PM, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPathfinder actually has a working one - for some definitions of \u0027working\u0027....\u00A0 (It can ship resources to vessels with a part to receive them with.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-07T16:02:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223553402\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551936697\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277770\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GoldForest\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, GoldForest said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I do not. I\u0027m not the mod author. And the author hasn\u0027t been on KSP in over a month. As for doing it myself, I have no modding experience really.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked through that thread and it seemed like people had been using it, but I didn\u2019t see a link.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are able to find it we may be able to get it working with Kerbal Konstructs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it would just be a prop, I don\u2019t know how to make it functional.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FormosaT_9","CreatedById":229418,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-12T04:30:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003Eseems like there are some drivers in\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EParaterraforming\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022207226\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7414864992\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/209162-paraterraforming-mod/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003Ebut I still want the one made by skykooler.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-12T04:32:06Z\u0022 title=\u002207/12/2023 04:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jul 12\u0022\u003EJuly 12, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by FormosaT_9\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}